hh3cDomain.name: hh3cDomain
hh3cDomain.contactinfo: Platform Team Hangzhou H3C Tech. Co., Ltd. Hai-Dian District Beijing P.R. China http://www.h3c.com Zip:100085
hh3cDomain.description: The MIB module is used for managing domain.

Hh3cModeOfDomainScheme.name: Hh3cModeOfDomainScheme
Hh3cModeOfDomainScheme.description: The scheme mode of the domain. none: indicates the domain has no scheme. local:indicates the domain will use local-server as a scheme. radius:indicates the domain will use radius scheme. tacacs:indicates the domain will use tacacs scheme. ldap:indicates the domain will use ldap scheme.

Hh3cAAATypeDomainScheme.name: Hh3cAAATypeDomainScheme
Hh3cAAATypeDomainScheme.description: The service type of the server.

Hh3cAccessModeofDomainScheme.name: Hh3cAccessModeofDomainScheme
Hh3cAccessModeofDomainScheme.description: The access mode of the domain.

hh3cDomainDefault.name: hh3cDomainDefault
hh3cDomainDefault.description: Specifies default domain on the equipment. Default value is 'system'.

hh3cDomainInfoEntry.name: hh3cDomainInfoEntry
hh3cDomainInfoEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) representing a domain.

hh3cDomainName.name: hh3cDomainName
hh3cDomainName.description: An index uniquely identifies a domain.

hh3cDomainState.name: hh3cDomainState
hh3cDomainState.description: The state of the domain, which reflects whether the domain is active. Default value is active.

hh3cDomainMaxAccessNum.name: hh3cDomainMaxAccessNum
hh3cDomainMaxAccessNum.description: The maximum number which the domain allows to access. If the value is set to 0, the access limit will be disabled.

hh3cDomainVlanAssignMode.name: hh3cDomainVlanAssignMode
hh3cDomainVlanAssignMode.description: The vlan assignment mode. The mode SHOULD be the same as the mode of corresponding server. 1 (integer) - Integer Vlan assignment mode. 2 (string) - String Vlan assignment mode. 3 (vlanlist) - VLAN-List Vlan assignment mode. The default value is integer.

hh3cDomainIdleCutEnable.name: hh3cDomainIdleCutEnable
hh3cDomainIdleCutEnable.description: The idle cut control. Setting this attribute to true, the connection will be cut when the flow is less than hh3cDomainIdleCutMinFlow and lasts hh3cDomainIdleCutMaxTime. Default value is false.

hh3cDomainIdleCutMaxTime.name: hh3cDomainIdleCutMaxTime
hh3cDomainIdleCutMaxTime.description: The maximal time of idle-cut. The unit is minute. If the value of hh3cDomainIdleCutEnable is false, the value of hh3cDomainIdleCutMaxTime is meaningless.

hh3cDomainIdleCutMinFlow.name: hh3cDomainIdleCutMinFlow
hh3cDomainIdleCutMinFlow.description: The minimal flow of idle-cut. The unit is byte. If the value of hh3cDomainIdleCutEnable is false, the value of hh3cDomainIdleCutMinFlow is meaningless.

hh3cDomainMessengerEnable.name: hh3cDomainMessengerEnable
hh3cDomainMessengerEnable.description: The messenger service control. If set hh3cDomainMessengerEnable to true, hh3cDomainMessengerLimitTime and hh3cDomainMessengerSpanTime must be set to valid values. Default value is false.

hh3cDomainMessengerLimitTime.name: hh3cDomainMessengerLimitTime
hh3cDomainMessengerLimitTime.description: The messenger service limit time. The unit is minute. If the value of hh3cDomainMessengerEnable is false, the value of hh3cDomainMessengerLimitTime is meaningless.

hh3cDomainMessengerSpanTime.name: hh3cDomainMessengerSpanTime
hh3cDomainMessengerSpanTime.description: The messenger service span time. The unit is minute. It must be a multiple of 5. If the value of hh3cDomainMessengerEnable is false, the value of hh3cDomainMessengerSpanTime is meaningless.

hh3cDomainSelfServiceEnable.name: hh3cDomainSelfServiceEnable
hh3cDomainSelfServiceEnable.description: The self service control. If set hh3cDomainSelfServiceEnable to true, hh3cDomainSelfServiceURL must be set to a valid value. Default value is FALSE.

hh3cDomainSelfServiceURL.name: hh3cDomainSelfServiceURL
hh3cDomainSelfServiceURL.description: Self-service URL(Uniform Resource Locator) of the domain.

hh3cDomainAccFailureAction.name: hh3cDomainAccFailureAction
hh3cDomainAccFailureAction.description: Defines the action that authentication should be taken if authentication succeeds but the associated accounting start fails. 1 (ignore) - treat as authentication success; ignore accounting start failure. 2 (reject) - treat as authentication failed if corresponding accounting start fails. Default value is reject.

hh3cDomainRowStatus.name: hh3cDomainRowStatus
hh3cDomainRowStatus.description: This object is responsible for managing the creation, deletion and modification of rows, which supports active status and CreateAndGo, Destroy operation. To destroy an existent row, the domain of the row MUST NOT be used by user.

hh3cDomainCurrentAccessNum.name: hh3cDomainCurrentAccessNum
hh3cDomainCurrentAccessNum.description: The current access number of the domain.

hh3cDomainIdleCutTime.name: hh3cDomainIdleCutTime
hh3cDomainIdleCutTime.description: Authentication aging time. If no packet is transmitted during the aging time, the authentication is aged out.

hh3cDomainSchemeTable.name: hh3cDomainSchemeTable
hh3cDomainSchemeTable.description: The (conceptual) table listing schemes of all domains.

hh3cDomainSchemeEntry.name: hh3cDomainSchemeEntry
hh3cDomainSchemeEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) representing an IP pool of a domain

hh3cDomainSchemeIndex.name: hh3cDomainSchemeIndex
hh3cDomainSchemeIndex.description: The scheme index of domain, which is an identifier of a domain scheme.

hh3cDomainSchemeMode.name: hh3cDomainSchemeMode
hh3cDomainSchemeMode.description: The scheme mode of the domain. Setting hh3cDomainSchemeMode to none(1) indicates the domain has none scheme. Setting hh3cDomainSchemeMode to local(2) indicates the domain will use local-server as a scheme. Setting hh3cDomainSchemeMode to radius(3), tacacs(4) or ldap(5) indicates the domain will use radius, tacacs or ldap scheme. If set hh3cDomainSchemeMode to radius(3), tacacs(4) or ldap(5), hh3cDomainAuthSchemeName and hh3cDomainAcctSchemeName must be set to valid values. And if hh3cDomainSchemeMode is set to none(1) or local(2), the value of hh3cDomainAuthSchemeName and hh3cDomainAcctSchemeName will be ignored.

hh3cDomainAuthSchemeName.name: hh3cDomainAuthSchemeName
hh3cDomainAuthSchemeName.description: The authentication scheme name of domain. If hh3cDomainSchemeMode is set to radius, tacacs or ldap, the hh3cDomainAuthSchemeName must be configured with a valid value.

hh3cDomainAcctSchemeName.name: hh3cDomainAcctSchemeName
hh3cDomainAcctSchemeName.description: The accounting scheme name of the domain. If hh3cDomainSchemeMode is set to radius or tacacs, the hh3cDomainAcctSchemeName must be configured with a valid value.

hh3cDomainSchemeRowStatus.name: hh3cDomainSchemeRowStatus
hh3cDomainSchemeRowStatus.description: This object is responsible for managing the creation, deletion and modification of rows, which supports active status and createAndGo, destroy operation. To create a new row, hh3cDomainSchemeMode must be specified. To destroy an existent row, the scheme of the row MUST NOT be used by user.

hh3cDomainSchemeAAAName.name: hh3cDomainSchemeAAAName
hh3cDomainSchemeAAAName.description: The scheme name of the domain, whether the scheme represents accounting, authentication or authorization references the object hh3cDomainSchemeAAAType. The value of the object must be valid if the value of hh3cDomainSchemeMode is radius or tacacs, the value of the object will be ignored if the value of hh3cDomainSchemeMode is none or local. If the domain has no scheme, there will be a null string. If this object is supported, the objects hh3cDomainAuthSchemeName and hh3cDomainAcctSchemeName will be ignored.

hh3cDomainSchemeAccessMode.name: hh3cDomainSchemeAccessMode
hh3cDomainSchemeAccessMode.description: The access mode of the domain scheme.

hh3cDomainIpPoolTable.name: hh3cDomainIpPoolTable
hh3cDomainIpPoolTable.description: The (conceptual) table listing IP pools of all domains.

hh3cDomainIpPoolEntry.name: hh3cDomainIpPoolEntry
hh3cDomainIpPoolEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) representing an IP pool of a domain.

hh3cDomainIpPoolNum.name: hh3cDomainIpPoolNum
hh3cDomainIpPoolNum.description: The number of IP pool, which is an identifier of an IP pool.

hh3cDomainIpPoolLowIpAddrType.name: hh3cDomainIpPoolLowIpAddrType
hh3cDomainIpPoolLowIpAddrType.description: The low IP addresses type (IPv4 or IPv6) of IP pool.

hh3cDomainIpPoolLowIpAddr.name: hh3cDomainIpPoolLowIpAddr
hh3cDomainIpPoolLowIpAddr.description: The low IP address of IP pool.

hh3cDomainIpPoolLen.name: hh3cDomainIpPoolLen
hh3cDomainIpPoolLen.description: The length of IP pool. Default value is 1.

hh3cDomainIpPoolRowStatus.name: hh3cDomainIpPoolRowStatus
hh3cDomainIpPoolRowStatus.description: This object is responsible for managing the creation, deletion and modification of rows, which supports active status and CreateAndGo, Destroy operation. To create a new row, hh3cDomainIpPoolNum and hh3cDomainIpPoolLowIpAddr must be specified. To destroy an existent row, the IP pool of this row MUST NOT be used by user.
